Intuition
When i looked at this problem i realized this is a sliding window problem with fixed window size of len(p) , An anagram contains exactly the same characters with the same frequencies as p ,so my initial intuition was to get the freq map of p , then find the freq map of initial window , if they are equal i will store index of low in result , else slide window and keep updating the created freq map of window and whenever the freq map of window equals to freq map of p append low in result.

Approach
calculate the target freq of p
calaculate inital window freq
if window_freq == target_freq:
append low in result

slide the window
add new element into window , update freq map of window , del low from from freq map , increase low , check if freq map becomes equal

return result

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(n)
Space complexity:
O(1)
Code
class Solution:
    def findAnagrams(self, s: str, p: str) -> List[int]:
        if len(p) > len(s):
            return []
        target_freq = {}
        for ch in p:
            target_freq[ch] = target_freq.get(ch,0) + 1
        
        window_freq = {}
        for i in range(len(p)):     
            window_freq[s[i]] = window_freq.get(s[i] ,0) + 1
        low = 0
        result = []

        
        if window_freq == target_freq:
            result.append(low)
        for high in range(len(p),len(s)):
            window_freq[s[high]] = window_freq.get(s[high],0) + 1
            window_freq[s[low]] -= 1
            if window_freq[s[low]] == 0:
                del window_freq[s[low]]
            low += 1
            if window_freq == target_freq:
                result.append(low)
        return result
